<div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
            
<p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
            
<p n="1-2">Third year of Nantipōttaraiyar.</p>
            
<p n="2-7">
               
<supplied reason="subaudible">There are</supplied> 200 
<supplied reason="subaudible">that is,</supplied> two hundred, 
<foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s of paddy that Pakaiccantiravicai Araiyaṉ, alias Kaṇavatimāṉ, 
<supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Vaṭuvūr in the Mīpuḷaināṭu, gave to cook and distribute 
<supplied reason="explanation">
  <foreign>aṭṭ-aḻiya</foreign>
</supplied> at the time/on the day 
<supplied reason="explanation">
  <foreign>nāṉṟu</foreign>
</supplied> 
<supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> 
<foreign>tiruvātirai</foreign>; 
<supplied reason="subaudible">this is for the food</supplied> for one hundred persons.
            </p>
            
         </div>
         
         
<div type="commentary">
            
<p n="1">On Nandivarman = Nandivarman III Pallava. See SII and IP.</p>
            
<p n="5">
<foreign>tiruvātirai</foreign>. A festival?</p>
            
<p n="7">
<foreign>nūṟṟuvar</foreign>. A corporate body ("the One Hundred")? Or one hundred people at random?</p>            
         </div>
         
         
